channel.title: [PI] Invisible Magic logs?
channel.description: I don't know if this is a client issue or server issue, but the Magic logs on my server are invisible. If anyone knows how to fix this problem, please tell me. :)

item.title: [PI] Invisible Magic logs?
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“xEvo, post:7, topic:342856”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=439262.msg3228067#msg3228067 date=1275782193]

I don’t know if this is a client issue or server issue, but the Magic logs on my server are invisible. If anyone knows how to fix this problem, please tell me.

I was thinking that, but I don’t really feel like looking through my cache for it.
Or someone accidentally replaced the magic log model to something else, and it’s rotated to such an angle that you can’t see the actual model.

Then download a new, empty cache to replace the fucked up one you have.
[/quote]
No thanks. :)[/quote]

Then stop fucking complaining. If you’re not willing to put in the effort, you don’t deserve to reap the rewards.
